## How to Use This Manual

This manual is the single source of truth for all exam coordination tasks at MSP. It is designed for both experienced coordinators and new starters.

**Structure:**
- Section 1: Quick Reference — contacts, systems, SAP transactions, key rules
- Section 2: Annual Timeline — what happens across the full academic year
- Section 3: Per-Period Checklist — a relative timeline tied to exam week
- Section 4: Detailed Procedures — step-by-step guides for every task
- Section 5: Syllabus / S+ Scheduling Manual — full system guide
- Section 6: SAP Grading Manual — full grading process
- Section 7: Email Templates — ready-to-use templates for all communications
- Section 8: Physical Checklists — exam carts, SPAR boxes, on-day operations
- Section 9: Operational Templates — print-ready instruction sheets

> ⚠️ **Deadlines in this manual are non-negotiable. Printing and transport logistics especially have zero tolerance for delays. When in doubt, act early.**

> 📌 The academic year runs across five exam periods: P1, P2, P4, and P5 have final exams. P3 and P6 are resit periods. Procedures repeat each period — use the Per-Period Checklist as your recurring guide.

