### 4.2 Schedule Check (Qualtrics)

> 📌 Done per period. Gathers exam format details from Course Coordinators. Note: can differ from the year plan overview. Access to Qualtrics required (personal login, via Lo-FSE).

**Step 1 — Send Qualtrics Link to CCs**
- Access: library.maastrichtuniversity.nl/apps-tools/qualtrics/
- Send the link to all CCs with a clear deadline
- **Midterm questions:** when does it take place, does it replace a teaching activity, duration, format
- **Final exam questions:** format, allowed aids (MUST BE SPECIFIC: calculator model, A5 scrap, notes, etc.), open or closed book
- No duration question for finals — UM policy is standard 2 hours

**Step 2 — Process Qualtrics Responses**
- Enter information into the exam overview document
- **File (English):** `J:\FSE_MSP\Secretariat\OSA\13. Scheduling P4\2024-2025\Exams\Overview mid-terms and exams Period 4`
- **File (Dutch, for Head Invigilators):** Toetsoverzicht MSP Final Exams P4 incl aantallen en bijzonderheden
- **Column J** = allowed aids for each exam (provided to Head Invigilators)
- File also records open/closed book status
- Retrieve SPAR students: run ZPIQ_REP_MOD_SPAR in SAP
  - Session codes: P1=100, P2=200, P4=400, P5=500
  - Enter module code, execute, scroll right for SPAR details
  - **If unclear:** run ZPIQ_REP_STUD_SPAR, execute, find student, scroll right for details
- Below the schedule: track who you received answers from and whether they want an overview

**Step 3 — Inform AR of Changes**
- If anything changed vs. the year plan (exam format, frame schedule) — inform AR (Anja Ronken)
- > ⚠️ **CHECK before sending. AR confirms if the change is possible. This is where rescheduling may happen.**

