## Section 5: Syllabus / S+ Scheduling Manual

> 📌 Syllabus ONLY works in Internet Explorer. Before opening: always run CleanEnterpriseProcessRebuildCERemoveImage from the Education server.  
> ⚠️ **Always Modify + Write Back (WB) to save changes. After any structural change: Unschedule → then Reschedule. If you don't, changes will not appear in MyTimetable.**

### 5.1 System Overview

- Login URL: http://syllabus.unimaas.nl/Scientia/Portal/Login.aspx
- Login with your UM account and password
- Select the correct academic year → click Enterprise Timetabler
- The system loads slowly — wait for it to fully open

### 5.2 Navigating to MSP Courses

- PROGRAMMES folder → correct year → semester → Courses → MSP
- Excel file in each folder contains overview of all courses + enrolled students

### 5.3 Tabs in Activity Templates

| Tab | Purpose |
|---|---|
| ID | Course information (name, duration, suggested time, day, planned size) |
| User text & tags | Add extra info for students (user text 2 & 3). Add tags 'My Timetable' and 'Published' |
| Planning | Group size, max students, create activities (use 'Make activities' button) |
| Allocate | Assign students to tutorials. Double-click in 'activity' column or use 'Allocate' button |
| Delivery & sequencing | Not normally used |
| Resource | All rooms and spaces — check availability via Timetable view |
| Pools | Not normally used |
| Availability | Week overview — select which weeks this activity runs |

### 5.4 Creating / Editing a Schedule Entry

**Step 1 — Set Up Activity**
- Find course in PROGRAMMES → select template → click Duplicate (do NOT overwrite the parent 'moeder' template)
- ID tab: Duration (in 15-min increments), Day, Suggested time, Planned size (optional)
- Give the activity a name (e.g. 'do 21.12')
- Click Modify → then WB (Write Back) to save regularly

**Step 2 — Set Availability (Weeks)**
- Availability tab → select the weeks this activity runs (use Ctrl to multi-select)
- To add a week not shown: click top-right box in ID screen → Availability: period (none) → extend weeks → Modify + WB

**Step 3 — Assign Resources (Room + Staff)**
- Resource tab → select lecturer (not all lecturers are in Syllabus — that's OK)
- To check room availability: Timetable view (top right) → tick room → if no reservations shown, room is free
- To find SBE rooms: choose SBE instead of CES/MSP top-left
- > ⚠️ **SBE rooms can only be reserved max 2 weeks before block start.**
- Select room → Modify + WB. Locations and staff must be on 'preset' status

**Step 4 — Schedule the Activity**
- Planning tab → double-click activity → Timetab → click grey block(s)
- Diamond/rhombus symbol = constraints satisfied → click Schedule
- If not: uncheck 'constraints' → choose time block → click Schedule → re-check constraints → WB
- User text: add any field trip notes in user text 2/3
- Tags: select 'My Timetable' on go-live date (UM-wide), 'My draft Timetable' before that
- Select 'Published' ONCE per course on the first lecture where ALL students are allocated — this writes back to SAP

**Step 5 — Allocate Students**
- Allocate tab → double-click 'activity' column or use 'Allocate' button
- For 2 groups: divide into upper and lower half of list → WB
- > 📌 If a student has a grey box and cannot be allocated: go to Planning → Unschedule → allocate student → re-schedule.

### 5.5 Making Changes to Existing Entries

**Remove a Date**
- Select correct template. Optionally rename it
- Availability tab → remove the week using Ctrl
- Planning → double-click activity → Timetab → Unschedule all → Reschedule
- Check all remaining weeks are still showing. If not: re-schedule everything
- SBE rooms: removed immediately. SSC rooms: remove via Outlook

**Add a Date**
- Select correct template. Optionally rename it
- Availability tab → add the week using Ctrl
- Planning → double-click activity → Timetab → Unschedule all → Reschedule
- Check all weeks are correct. Don't forget to book the room for the new week!

**All Other Changes**
- Make the change, then always Unschedule → Reschedule. Otherwise it won't appear in Timetable
- Remember to update the room as well if relevant

### 5.6 Sharing Staff / Rooms Across Faculties

**Sharing a Staff Member**
- Timetabler → Staff → find lecturer in left column → Constraint → tick the correct faculty → Modify + WB

**Sharing a Room**
- Timetabler → Locations → select room → Constraints → tick faculty → Modify + WB

### 5.7 Checking Room Availability (Quick Method)

- In Timetable (read-only view): click Location View (top right)
- Select individual rooms or entire buildings
- Set view to Availability to quickly see what is free
- > 📌 Timetable is read-only — you cannot book or change anything in Timetable. All bookings must be done in Syllabus/S+.

