## Section 6: SAP Grading Manual

> 📌 Check and update this section once per year after the new EER and R&R has been set. Location: `J:\FSE_MSP\Secretariat\OSA\30. Procedures\BoE\R&R and EER`  
> ⚠️ **CRITICAL ROUNDING RULE: Grades between 5.45 and 5.49 round DOWN to 5.4, which is a FAIL. Do not round up to 5.5.**

### 6.1 General Grading Rules

- All grades on a scale of 1–10, rounded to 1 decimal (nearest decimal)
- Grades below 5.5 = fail on transcript
- No participation OR missing partial assessment = NG (not graded) = fail on transcript
- Sufficient overall grade + attendance fail = fail on transcript
- Attendance 70–85%: student may compensate via additional assignment
- CC deadline: 10 working days from Friday of exam week
- OSA has 5 additional working days to process after CC deadline
- OSA publishes final results in Student Portal within 15 working days after last exam date
- Transcripts of all active students must be updated within 1 working day after final publication deadline
- One working day after ALL grades come in: update all transcripts of all active students

> 📌 In this section, 'course' includes practicals, projects, and theses.

### 6.2 Reminder Schedule for Late Grades

| When | Action |
|---|---|
| 1 day before CC's 10-working-day deadline | Send first reminder to CC |
| 2–3 days after CC's deadline | Send second reminder to CC |
| After final 15-working-day OSA publication deadline | OSA sends final reminder on behalf of Leon de Windt. Inform Leon and ask permission first |
| Any late entries | Discuss with team and Board of Examiners — late grades affect other processes |

### 6.3 Preparing the Grading File (ZPIQ_EXPORT_APPR)

**Step 1 — Export Appraisals to Excel**
- SAP transaction: ZPIQ_EXPORT_APPR
- Fill: course code, academic year, period
- Do NOT tick 'Exam Only'
- Fill appraiser and appraisal date:
  - For exams/resits arranged by OSA: use the exact exam date
  - For all other courses (no exam/resit set by OSA): use the last Friday of exam week
  - For RESIT period (P1, P2, P4, P5): for resits arranged by OSA = exact date; for others = last date of specific resit period
- > ⚠️ **To update the appraiser (current grader), contact Eva Nelissen. See: `J:\FSE_MSP\Secretariat\OSA\30. Procedures\Appraiser`**
- Execute → file saved to C:\TEMP
- Copy CSV export file to applicable J-drive folder
- Send email with instructions and deadline to CC. Attach: empty Excel sheet + SAP manual
- **Email templates:** `J:\FSE_MSP\Secretariat\OSA\30. Procedures\Grades\First sit\e-mail templates`
- **Instructions for CCs:** `J:\FSE_MSP\Secretariat\OSA\30. Procedures\Grades\First sit\Bijlages`

### 6.4 Checking the Received Excel Sheet

- Attendance column: must be P (pass), F (fail), or NG (not graded)
- Grades column: must be rounded to 1 decimal
- If incorrect: email CC with instructions on how to fill in the SAP file
- **Save Excel file to:** J-drive applicable folder AND local desktop folder (import must be done from local location, not server)

### 6.5 Importing Grades (ZPIQ_IMPORT_APPR)

**Step 1 — Simulation Run First**
- SAP transaction: ZPIQ_IMPORT_APPR
- 'Input File': select Excel file from the DESKTOP folder (not server)
- Leave 'Test' ticked → Execute (this is a simulation — no grades saved yet)
- Review: if no errors and system confirms all grades processed successfully → proceed to step 2
- > ⚠️ **If errors appear: correct the Excel file before proceeding.**

**Step 2 — Official Run**
- Untick 'Test' → Execute
- This is the official run — grades are now processed and saved in SAP

### 6.6 Calculating and Publishing Final Grades (ZPIQSMFU_CALC)

**Step 1 — Run Grade Calculation**
- SAP transaction: ZPIQSMFU_CALC
- Fill course code. AY and session auto-fill
- Click 'Students' → students appear
- Click 'Attendance' → verify upload is correct
- Click 'Grade Supervisor' → verify grades uploaded correctly
- Click 'Final Result' → verify final results uploaded correctly
- Select ALL students: top-left icon in table
- Click calculator icon in menu bar (1)
- Click 'Accord' (2) → 'Block' (3) → 'Save' (4)
- Results are now published in the Student Portal
- Update the resit overview

### 6.7 Updating Individual Student Grades (ZPIQSTFU)

> 📌 Use when a single student's grade changes later — for example, after an additional assignment or late grade submission.

**Step 1 — Update a Single Student**
- SAP transaction: ZPIQSTFU (Student follow-up, entry results)
- Fill student number
- Fill academic year and period → Search
- Double-click on the course concerned
- Adjust attendance AND grade in the 'Grade Symbol' column
- Grade must be added to the 'Grade Supervisor' row
- Select 'Final Result' line
- Click calculator icon → select all lines (box next to description) → Accord → Block → Save
- Results are now updated and published

### 6.8 Downloading Partial Grades from Canvas

**Step 1 — Export Partial Grades**
- Canvas → SIS Imported courses → search and select course
- Click 'Grades' → the gradebook appears
- Click 'Actions' → Export → CSV file created
- Open file from Downloads folder → select column A
- If all data in one column: use Text to Columns → Delimited → Comma → Finish
- Final grades column shows 2 decimals (percentage to grade). Paste in SAP/CSV file and round to 1 decimal
- Save alongside the SAP import file in the course folder
- > 📌 Check if partial grades are published in Canvas. If not: email CC to upload them.

